DIY litter box room for multiple cats

images.description: Super easy build! Only cost about $60ish to build in total! It rolls out and we keep their bowls stored up there as a reminder to clean the box! It’s right underneath our staircase and we have a barn door we built for less than $50 that covers it.

What we had before. Gross and wasn’t easy to keep clean. We knew we didn’t have enough litter boxes for the amount of cats so we just built one really big one! Happier cats, happier life.

If anyone wants to know how we built it just message me and I’ll tell you a step-by-step! Sorry I didn’t take pictures in between!
Figured I could at least post something for once in my life, they're my babies
Happiest cat in the world right now!

Hi Imgurians! I’m a long-time lurker and was encouraged by my boyfriend, who introduced me to Imgur, to share some of my OC.  I started doing these illustrations (or doodles) to pass the time in quarantine and to distract my brain. Sharing them has been a great way to track my progress with drawing and meet new people. I share all these guys on Instagram (@sonderslurp), but for some reason never shared them here—because I was a bit intimidated—I really enjoy scrolling through imgur and have grown to love both the community and platform—so here goes my turn to contribute!
